<<<explanation>>>: The firstKey() method returns the first key in the sorted map.

A: The firstKey() method is defined in the Map interface, not the SortedMap interface.
You can use the following code to get the first key in the map:
SortedMap<Integer, Character> memory = new TreeMap<>();
memory.put(1, 'a');
memory.put(2, 'b');
memory.put(3, 'c');

Integer firstKey = memory.firstKey();
System.out.println(firstKey); // Output: 1
